textAfterTable: palmbob Acton, CA (Zone 8b) August 30, 2010 11:47 PM Post #8072026 few if any would try to steal a Macrozamia- most would not recognize them as cycads, first of all, and if they did, it is unlikely any would be interested in going through the effort of taking them unless they were incredibly old, large and standing out (like in a nice pot). Never heard of one of these being stolen in southern California. As for the more obvious species (most Encephalartos), best way to keep them from being taken is to make them difficult to take- plant them behind a row of spiny things, put in back yard with a large dog, pile huge rocks around them making digging nearly impossible, etc. You cannot post until you register, login and subscribe.
